==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[refutare]]''

===Pronunciation===
American ([[SAMPA]]): [r@"fjut]
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːt|-uːt]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|refut|ing}}

# To [[prove]] (something) to be [[false]] or [[incorrect]].
# (''Erroneous'') To [[deny]] the [[truth]] or [[correctness]] of (something).

====Usage notes====
*  To refute a proposition is to show beyond argument that it is false.  
The erroneous use of "refute" to mean "to deny" is contrary to the essence of the word, and best avoided by those who value precision in language. A better alternative in such a context would be "repudiate," which means to reject or refuse to acknowledge, but without the implication of justification.

